As Nigeria begins Covid-19 Vaccine administration on Friday 5th March, President Muhammadu Buhari, Vice President, Yemi Osinbajo as well as the Secretary to Government of the Federation (SGF) and Chairman of the Presidential Task Force on the COVID-19 pandemic, Mr. Boss Mustapha will publicly receive their first jab of the COVID-19 vaccine on Saturday.  Speaking on the planned roll-out of the vaccines at the Presidential Villa, Abuja, the Executive Director, National Primary Health Care Development Agency (NPHDA), Dr. Faisal Shuiab. who disclosed this said this move is to increase public confidence and overcome vaccine hesitancy, as current study revealed that only about 50% of Nigerians say they would definitely take the vaccine.  Earlier, the Minister of Health, Dr Osagie Ehanire said the current preventive strategies must be sustained to further stop the spread of the virus.Â NAFDAC DG, Professor Mojisola Adeyeye and the DG NCDC, Dr Chikwe Ihekwaezu said investing in national health security, driving risk communications, as well as effective surveillance, will be sustained to check substandard vaccines. 